"Baumer M., Großmann O., Miedaner H., Graf H., Sacher B.","Kernel abnormalities in malting barley - Determining terminology and assessment [Kornanomalien bei Braugerste - Begriffsbestimmung und Bewertung]",1998,"Monatsschrift fur Brauwissenschaft","51","11-12",,"176","188",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0007197950&partnerID=40&md5=1abde39e8e868640158639415fb0573c","Bayer, Landesanstalt Bodenkultur/P., Postfach 1641, D-85316 Freising, Germany","Baumer, M.; Großmann, O., Bayer, Landesanstalt Bodenkultur/P., Postfach 1641, D-85316 Freising, Germany; Miedaner, H.; Graf, H.; Sacher, B.","Kernel abnormalities are favourably influenced by extreme weather conditions in the corn ripening phase. Frequent occurence of such phenomena has to be taken into consideration should there be a change in climate in central Europe due global warming. Abnormalities of kernels can inhibit the utilization of malting barley. Because of the varying importance in malting and brewing technology, each phenomena must be clearly separated from one another. Differences are made between grain with split kernels, incomplete overlapping of husks, damaged husks, second tillering and pre-harvest sprouting. As well as the environmental effects, genetic variability also becomes apparent which is valuable for the determination of plant breeding and variety selection. Influences of technical production can significantly increase or even reduce the risk but are relatively insignificant when compared with the overall variability. The breeding of early ripening varieties should be encouraged, not only because of its relation to second tillering. Examination conditions in barley breeding and variety authorisation should be modified to favour early ripening varieties.",,,,,,,,"Baumer, M., Warum Gerstenkörner aufspringen (1995) Pflanzenschutzpraxis, 1, pp. 42-43; Baumer, M., Aigner, A., Aufgesprungene Körner erschwerten 1991 die Vermarktung der Braugerste - Das Risiko Läßt sich Verringern (1992) Bayer. Landw. Wochenblatt, 3, pp. 35-36; Gaebel, O., Neuartige Beschädigungen an Braugerste (1934) Wochenschrift für Brauerei, 13, p. 101; Leopold, H., Horak, W., Studium neuartiger Beschädigungen an der Braugerste (1935) Wochenschrift für Brauerei, 51, pp. 409-414; N, N., Brautechnologische Analysenmethoden, Band I, Methodensammlung der Mitteleuropäischen Brautechnischen Analysenkommission (MEBAK) (1997) Selbstverlag der MEBAK; Oberforster, M., Werteker, M., Aufplatzen der Körner- Unsicherheit im Braugerstenanbau (1998) Inform, Zeitschrift für Pflanzenzüchtung und Saatgutproduktion, 1, pp. 26-29; Schulz, K.G., Neuartige Beschädigungen an Braugerste (1934) Wochenschrift für Brauerei, 6, pp. 42-45","Bayer, Landesanstalt Bodenkultur/P., Postfach 1641, D-85316 Freising, Germany",,,,,,,,07231520,,,,"German","Monatsschr. Brauwiss.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0007197950
